-- UN Security Council Schedules Emergency Meeting on Egypt Today
-- B y   S a n g w o n   Y o o n
-- 2013-08-15T19:12:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-15/un-security-council-schedules-emergency-meeting-on-egypt-today.html
The United Nations Security Council
will hold a closed emergency meeting on the situation in  Egypt 
today at 5:30 p.m. in New York, according to an announcement
from the UN press office.  Deputy Secretary-General Jan Eliasson will brief the
council, according to the announcement. The U.K., France and
Australia called earlier today for an urgent Security Council
meeting on the violence in Egypt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sangwon Yoon in United Nations at 
 syoon32@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Drummond at 
 bdrummond@bloomberg.net  